 25  /- `val_le_mul_left` is often not a required in definitions of a euclidean
 26    domain since given the other properties we can show there is a
 27    (noncomputable) euclidean domain α with the property `val_le_mul_left`.
 28    So potentially this definition could be split into two different ones
 29    (euclidean_domain_weak and euclidean_domain_strong) with a noncomputable
 30    function from weak to strong. I've currently divided the lemmas into
 31    strong and weak depending on whether they require `val_le_mul_left` or not. -/
